properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 1:30AM PST until January 13 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Scattered snow showers are possible with 1 or 2 inches of
snow possible this morning. Snow fell in some areas overnight.
Expect locally slick travel conditions this morning.

* WHERE...Far southwest Mason County and the interior lowlands
of Grays Harbor County, including Matlock, McCleary, and
Montesano.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM PST THIS MORNING
